@startuml runLocalModule Sequence Diagram
!theme plain
skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center
skinparam responseMessageBelowArrow true
skinparam maxMessageSize 150

title Eureka CLI - runLocalModule Command Flow

actor Developer
participant "CLI" as CLI
participant "Run" as Run
participant "Keycloak" as Keycloak
participant "ManagementSvc" as Mgmt
participant "Build Tool\n(Maven / Gradle / Grails)" as Build
participant "Docker" as Docker
participant "ModuleSvc" as ModSvc
participant "HTTPClient" as HTTP
participant "Kong Gateway" as Kong

Developer -> CLI: eureka-cli runLocalModule\n--modulePath /path/to/private-module\n[--applicationName app-local]

activate CLI
CLI -> Run: New(action.RunLocalModule)
activate Run

== Authentication & Context Setup ==
Run -> Run: setKeycloakMasterAccessTokenIntoContext()
Run -> Keycloak: POST /realms/master/protocol/openid-connect/token
Keycloak --> Run: Access Token
note right: Get Keycloak master access token\nusing client credentials

Run -> Run: resolveModuleIdentity()
note right: If --moduleName / --moduleVersion\nomitted, derive from pom.xml /\nbuild.gradle(.kts) / gradle.properties

Run -> Run: setDefaultNamespaceIntoContext()
note right: Set namespace to foliolocal\nif not specified

== Collision Guard ==
Run -> Mgmt: GetLatestApplication(baseAppName)
Mgmt -> Kong: GET /applications?appName=<base>&latest=1&full=true
Kong --> Mgmt: Base Application
Mgmt --> Run: modules[] of base app

alt module name already in base app
    Run --> CLI: Error: "<name> is already\nprovided by <base app>;\nuse upgradeModule instead"
    CLI --> Developer: X Aborted (nothing changed)
end

== Module Build Phase ==
opt !skipModuleArtifact
    Run -> Run: buildModuleArtifact()
    Run -> Build: detectModuleBuild(modulePath)
    Build --> Run: {tool, dir}
    Run -> Build: clean + set version + package/assemble
    Build --> Run: Artifact + ModuleDescriptor.json
    note right: Reuses upgrademodulesvc\nBuildModuleArtifact
end

opt !skipModuleImage
    Run -> Run: buildModuleImage()
    Run -> Docker: docker build\n--tag foliolocal/<module>:<version>
    Docker --> Run: Image Built
end

Run -> Run: readModuleDescriptor()
note right: Read ModuleDescriptor.json from\ntarget/ or build/resources/main/

== Module Deployment Phase ==
opt !skipModuleDeployment
    Run -> Run: reserveUsedHostPorts()
    Run -> Docker: list running containers
    Docker --> Run: published host ports
    note right: Skip ports already in use so a second\nlocal module does not collide

    Run -> Run: deployLocalModuleAndSidecarPair()
    Run -> ModSvc: NewModulePair()
    ModSvc --> Run: Module Pair
    Run -> ModSvc: DeployModuleAndSidecarPair()
    ModSvc -> Docker: Deploy Module Container
    Docker --> ModSvc: Module Running
    ModSvc -> Docker: Deploy Sidecar Container
    Docker --> ModSvc: Sidecar Running
    ModSvc --> Run: Deployment Complete
end

== Application Update Phase (app-local) ==
Run -> Mgmt: GetLatestApplicationByName(app-local)
Mgmt -> Kong: GET /applications?appName=app-local&latest=1&full=true
Kong --> Mgmt: app-local (or none)
Mgmt --> Run: Existing app-local | none

alt app-local does NOT exist
    Run -> Run: buildInitialLocalApp()
    note right: New app-local-1.0.0 with:\n dependencies: [<base app>]\n modules: [this module]\n uiModules: []
else app-local already exists
    Run -> Run: mergeLocalApp()
    note right: Increment patch version.\nMerge module by name\n(append or replace).\n**Preserve existing\nuiModules / uiModuleDescriptors\nverbatim.**
end

opt !skipApplication
    Run -> HTTP: POST /applications?check=true
    HTTP -> Kong: Create app-local-<newVersion>
    Kong --> HTTP: Application Created
    HTTP --> Run: Application Response
end

== Module Discovery ==
opt !skipModuleDiscovery
    Run -> HTTP: POST /modules/discovery
    HTTP -> Kong: Register <module>-sc.eureka:<port>
    Kong --> HTTP: Discovery Registered
    HTTP --> Run: Discovery Response

    alt Discovery Failed
        Run -> Run: cleanupLocalAppOnFailure()
        note right: Rollback:\n- If app-local was newly created:\n   DELETE app-local-<newVersion>\n- If app-local existed:\n   keep previous version
    end
end

== Tenant Entitlement ==
opt !skipTenantEntitlement
    alt app-local was newly created
        Run -> HTTP: POST /entitlements?async=false
        HTTP -> Kong: Attach tenants to app-local-<newVersion>
    else app-local existed (upgrade)
        Run -> HTTP: PUT /entitlements?async=false
        HTTP -> Kong: Upgrade tenants to app-local-<newVersion>
    end
    Kong --> HTTP: Flow ID
    HTTP --> Run: OK

    alt Entitlement Failed
        Run -> Run: cleanupLocalAppOnFailure()
        note right: Same rollback branch as above
    end
end

== Cleanup ==
Run -> Mgmt: RemoveApplications(app-local, keep=<newVersion>)
Mgmt -> Kong: DELETE previous app-local-<oldVersion>
Kong --> Mgmt: Deleted

opt cleanup
    Run -> Build: revert version + clean
    Build --> Run: Workspace reset
end

Run --> CLI: Success
deactivate Run
CLI --> Developer: OK - Local module running under app-local-<newVersion>
deactivate CLI

@enduml